                            <comment id="14455091" author="endarkened" created="Fri, 11 Nov 2011 06:41:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh, accidentally clicked Enter... I&apos;ll finish description here.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While error message is formatted by the following sequence:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;throw new ClientException(&lt;br/&gt;
						&quot;Timeout while waiting for system to be complied to expected condition:\r\nFlags:&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
								+ expectedClientState.flagsToString()&lt;br/&gt;
								+ &quot;\r\nRoster:&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
								+ expectedClientState.rosterToString()&lt;br/&gt;
								+ &quot;\r\n&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
								+ expectedClientState.incomingStanzasToString()&lt;br/&gt;
								+ &quot;\nCurrent set of states:\r\nFlags:&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
								+ getState().flagsToString()&lt;br/&gt;
								+ &quot;\r\nRoster:&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
								+ expectedClientState.rosterToString());&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This does not happen if I run tests simply using testng.jar lib - message is being written just fine.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14455145" author="krosenvold" created="Wed, 16 Nov 2011 14:01:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is the intended behaviour, the one-line summaries truncate newlines. To make this clearer I added (..) after truncated messages in r1202865. To see the full messages you need to look at the build result files.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14455093" author="endarkened" created="Thu, 17 Nov 2011 01:51:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As far as I understand, this was made to truncate stack trace output in the results, right? Why don&apos;t you let user decide, if he wants to see multi-sting messages or not by defining it in &amp;lt;configuration/&amp;gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14455199" author="krosenvold" created="Thu, 17 Nov 2011 03:28:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Historically, there has been &lt;b&gt;nothing&lt;/b&gt; regarding the reason for the failure. For the last few versions, it has been tweaked to give this &quot;overview&quot; effect; it&apos;s an overview, and it might even be trimmed to not contain the first whole line. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you want to request your desired behaviour as a new feature, go ahead. But it is not a bug.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14455163" author="endarkened" created="Thu, 17 Nov 2011 03:35:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17994192" author="olamy" created="Fri, 4 Jul 2025 07:17:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This project has moved from Jira to GitHub Issues. This issue was migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-surefire/issues/1804&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;apache/maven-surefire#1804&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
